Songun Politics Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Meetings, a film show and book, photo and handicraft exhibitions and art performances took place in Austria and the Czech Republic and at Siberian State University of Communications in Russia and the Mongolian Art Gallery from Feb. 14 to 16 on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed at the exhibitions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, photos showing their undying feats and books, photos and handicrafts introducing the achievements of the Korean people in socialist construction and their talent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean film "The Great Leader Steers the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation to Victory" was screened at the film show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stages of the art performances were Korean songs and songs and dances of the relevant countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Austrian preparatory committee to commemorate the Day of the Sun and February 16 in 2007 in his speech at a meeting said Kim Jong Il has turned the DPRK into a country strong in ideology and military force with his unique Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an expression of the highest praise of the progressive humankind for the undying feats performed by Kim Jong Il for the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence that he was awarded the "International Kim Il Sung Prize," he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting in Austria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the chairman of the Egyptian Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea published the article "The Sun of Korea Will Shine Always" in the Internet homepage of the U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics on the occasion of the February Holiday, in which he said, under Kim Jong Il's Songun politics, the DPRK is turning into a socialist fortress and the revolutionary cause of Kim Il Sung being brought into a brilliant reality.

Materials on Songun Politics Widely Disseminated among S. Korean Youth and Students 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification is widely disseminating "20 Questions and Answers on Songun Politics," a collection of materials explaining Songun politics, among youth and students through Internet, according to a media report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The collection explains in the form of questions and answers the essence and originality, validity and vitality of Songun politics so that young people from all walks of life and students may make an effective use of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The collection calls for positively supporting and upholding Songun politics.

Japan's Dangerous Drive to Become Military Giant Debunked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Japan launched again an H-2A rocket loaded with information and optical satellites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, a news analyst of Rodong Sinmun Monday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The full-dressed launching of spy satellites by Japan under the plausible cloak of "scientific researches" goes to prove that its moves for turning itself into a military giant and staging reinvasion have reached a dangerous phase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries have not abandoned even a moment their old dream of "the Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere" which fizzled out in the past. Now they are putting spurs to the building of a military power in a bid to realize it in the new century at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are working to throw a spy satellite network in the space to commit espionage against the DPRK and other countries and round off preparations for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's madcap launching of spy satellites is a criminal act of gravely menacing peace and stability in the Korean Peninsula and Asia as it is a link in the whole chain of its ever-more open moves for reinvasion of the region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ever growing is the danger of Japan's scheme to throw a network of spy satellites in the space under the excuse of advance detection of someone's "threat" and "military action" and use it in its overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite natural for the peace-loving progressives of the world to heighten vigilance against Japan's launching of spy satellites and moves to become a military giant, watching them on alert. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should face up to the watchful eyes of the world and give up its drive for building a military power and venturing overseas expansion.

NA Urged Not to Ratify Humiliating Agreement 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- At least 910 figures of all strata including political, labor and educational circles in south Korea reportedly issued the second declaration on Feb. 26 urging the "National Assembly" (NA) not to ratify the humiliating special agreement on sharing the funds for the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the above-mentioned special agreement is now under discussion at the NA, the declaration said that it calls on south Korea to pay 725.5 billion won or 6.6 percent more than last year for the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea this year and it also envisages the offer of a larger amount of money to the U.S. forces according to the expected commodity price soaring in 2008. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a treacherous action as it runs counter to the desire of the people from all walks of life for the relaxation of the military tensions and the establishment of a peace-keeping mechanism on the Korean Peninsula, it noted, urging the NA to refuse to ratify the special agreement and adopt a resolution demanding the "government" renegotiate it with the U.S.

Preserving National Character Essential for Socialist Cultural Construction: Rodong Sinmun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Preserving national identity and well keeping alive what is national are highly important in ushering in a period of all-round efflorescence in all aspects of socialist cultural construction, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Keeping alive what is national in cultural construction means properly preserving and constantly carrying forward and developing the excellent cultural tradition peculiar to the nation in conformity with the demand and interests of the revolution and the people of the country. This is the basic guarantee for firmly maintaining the Juche character and national identity in cultural construction and thoroughly embodying what is national in social life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership of the Party and the leader the Korean people are today further developing what is national in socialist cultural construction and national culture and morale of life suitable to their sentiments and feelings are prevailing across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Revolutionary and popular literature and arts of our era national in style and socialist in content have been newly created and what is national is actively encouraged in the social life of the Korean people ranging from lingual life to etiquette and morality and dietary life under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il who is demonstrating national dignity and honor to the whole world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation-first spirit fully represents the revolutionary will and stand of the Korean people to constantly carry forward and develop what is national in socialist cultural construction and highly display the dignity and honor of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  In dressing, singing and dancing today, the Koreans do them to suit the superior custom and way of life of the nation and national sentiments and fragrance and they are giving full play to the noble national traits of helping each other and leading each other along and living in harmony, wherever they may reside. Wholesome moral traits and way of life based on revolutionary comradeship, sense of obligation and revolutionary conscience have become a social fashion. This is the proud reality of our country where socialist national culture is in full bloom.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Russia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Workers' Party of Korea Organizes and Guides All the Victories of Our People" was brought out in booklet on Feb. 16 by a printing house in Nakhodka, Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on Oct. 3, Juche 79 (1990), clarifies the idea that the guidance of a party serves as a decisive guarantee for the victory of the socialist cause. Expounded in it are also the issue of strengthening the Workers' Party of Korea into a revolutionary party of Juche type and the basic ways for the Party to fulfill its mission and duty as a leading political organization.

Kim Ki Nam Meets New Russian Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, met and had a conversation with Valery Sukhinin, new Russian ambassador to the DPRK, who paid a courtesy call on him Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Pak Kyong Son, vice department director of the WPK Central Committee, and Alexandr Matsegora, minister-councilor of the Russian embassy here.

Japanese Reactionaries' Suppression of Chongryon Denounced in Nepal 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- The Nepal-Korea Friendship Association, the Institute for the Juche Studies, the Association for Supporting the Songun Politics, the Journalist Association, the Peace Action Committee, the National Press Club, the Study Forum for Self-Reliance, the Baktapur Society for Korea Study and the Committee for Supporting the Reunification of Korea of Nepal made public a joint statement on Feb. 26, denouncing the Japanese reactionaries' suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement accused the Japanese authorities of arresting Koreans in Japan without any ground while searching organizations under Chongryon, schools and dwelling houses of Koreans and floating distorted reports to impair the image of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We regard such brutal suppression as an intolerable infringement upon the sovereignty of the DPRK, a dignified socialist country, and an unprecedented crime, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It strongly demanded the Japanese authorities immediately stop the frantic anti-Chongryon campaign and suppression of Koreans in Japan and truly respect and protect the Koreans in Japan with historical and moral sense of obligation.

South Korean Organization Flails Suppression of Koreans in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity to Implement the June 15 Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly said it would fight against the Japanese authorities' suppression of Koreans in Japan with the wisdom, valor and united strength of the Korean nation displayed in the March First Popular Uprising against the Japanese imperialists, the robbers, for independence and dignity, the life of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization in its statement on March 1, the 88th anniversary of the uprising, noted that the Japanese authorities were escalating their suppression of Koreans in Japan under the pretext of the north's nuclear deterrent for self-defense. This reveals their foolish dream to gratify again their ambition for aggression on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Northeast Asia, it added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The entire Korean nation, it said, should carry forward the spirit of national independence and patriotic spirit of resistance displayed in the March First Popular Uprising and thus glorify the June 15 era of reunification by attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity.

Japanese Authorities' Suppression Protested
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- A meeting of Koreans in Japan was held in Tokyo on Mar. 3 to denounce the Japanese authorities' unjust political suppression and human rights abuses against the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Chairman So Man Sul, Chief Vice-Chairman Ho Jong Man and vice-chairmen, the secretary general and advisers of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter charged that though 88 years have passed after the March First Popular Uprising, the descendants of the Japanese imperialist war criminals have not yet redressed for the crimes they committed against the Korean nation generation after generation, but are still hell-bent on the crackdown upon Chongryon and Korean residents in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With a wicked political scheme, the Japanese authorities have disallowed entry of the DPRK ship "Mangyongbong-92" into a Japanese port while making desperate efforts to suffocate Chongryon and Koreans in Japan through a chauvinist campaign for persecution and illegal oppression of Korean nationals, he pointed out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He strongly demanded that the Japanese government stop at once its anti-DPRK policy, political suppression and human rights abuses against the Korean residents, which go against the international political trend. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting, indignation speeches were made by Pak Chang Gil, chairman of the Tokyo Metropolitan Headquarters of Chongryon, O Jae Se, director-general of the Korean Federation of Workers in Commerce in Japan, Ryang Ok Chul, vice-chairwoman of the Korean Democratic Women's Union in Japan, and Kim Cha Dol, director of the General Affairs Department of the Korean Youth League in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also solidarity speeches were made by Sumiko Shimizu, representative of the Japanese Women's Society for Solidarity with the Korean Women, Prof. Kenichi Asano, lawyer Shigeru Tokoi and Song Se Il, secretary general of the Alliance of South Koreans in Japan for Democracy and National Unification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal to all Koreans in Japan was read out at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And introduced were messages of encouragement from 54 public organizations in south Korea, six organizations of overseas Koreans and Japanese personages from different standings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then So Chung On, director of the International Department of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee, gave a briefing on his activities. He participated in the "information meeting and seminar on the human rights abuses against Korean students in Japan" held in south Korea on Feb. 28. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Introduced were placards carrying such letters as "The Japanese authorities, lift the sanctions against the DPRK and repeal the hostile policy towards it!" and "Immediately stop national discrimination and persecution against the Koreans in Japan!" which were sent in a joint name by four organizations of south Korea, including the Reunification Solidarity and the Democratic Labor Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written protest and appeal to the Japanese government and people were adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meeting a grand march of Koreans in Japan was staged in denunciation of the Japanese authorities' unjust political suppression and human rights abuses against Chongryon and Korean residents in Japan.

Kim Jong Il visita la embajada china en Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 5 de marzo (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, visito la vispera la Embajada de la Republica Popular China en Corea cumplimentando una invitacion del embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario chino en ocasion del 15 de enero segun el calendario lunar, fiesta folclorica comun de ambos paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Le acompanaron el secretario del CC del PTC Kim Ki Nam, el primer vicecanciller Kang Sok Ju, el primer subjefe de departamento del CC del PTC Ri Yong Chol, el consejero del CDN de la RPDC Kim Yang Gon, los generales de ejercito del EPC Kim Jong Gak y Hyon Chol Hae, el coronel general Choe Pu Il, el vicecanciller Kim Yong Il y el subjefe de departamento del CC del PTC Pak Kyong Son. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Dirigente fue acogido por el embajador Liu Xiaoming y otros funcionarios directivos de la sede diplomatica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Todos los miembros de la embajada dieron al Dirigente calida bienvenida, uno de los cuales le obsequio un ramo de flores fragantes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tras agradecer la invitacion, el Dirigente felicito a los miembros de la embajada por la fiesta. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En la ocasion, el embajador chino transmitio al Dirigente las palabras orales enviadas por Hu Jintao, Secretario General del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de China y Presidente de la RPCh y le rindio presente preparado por si mismo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Dirigente departio con el embajador quien ofrecio una recepcion en honor del primero. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Este dia, el Dirigente tomo una foto de recuerdo junto con todos los miembros de la embajada china.

Rodong Sinmun critica lanzamiento de satelites espias por Japon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 5 de marzo (ATCC) -- Hace poco, Japon volvio a lanzar el cohete "H-2A" dotado de un satelite artificial optico y el otro para la recogida de informaciones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El lanzamiento de esos aparatos espias, que se impulsa activamente so pretexto de "investigacion cientifica", comprueba que entran en una etapa peligrosa las maniobras del pais isleno encaminadas a erigirse como una potencia militar y tomar de nuevo el camino de agresion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Senala asi el rotativo Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual del 5 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los reaccionarios japoneses no quieren dejar nunca su ambicion de la "esfera de coprosperidad de la gran Asia Oriental", que no pudieron materializar en el siglo pasado, y dan acicate a los preparativos para convertirse en una potencia militar a fin de realizarla sin falta en el nuevo siglo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el mismo contexto, tratan de ultimar los preparativos para la agresion a ultramar cometiendo actos de espionaje sobre Corea y otros paises a traves de la red de satelites espias establecida en el espacio cosmico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por tal razon, siendo un eslabon de las maniobras de Japon para la nueva agresion a la Peninsula Coreana y el resto de Asia, el lanzamiento de citados satelites deviene un crimen que amenaza gravemente la paz y la estabilidad del area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Adquieren cada vez mas peligrosidad tales maniobras que se cometen bajo pretextos de la "amenaza" de alguien y el reconocimiento previo sobre las "acciones militares" de este. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Por eso, los pueblos progresistas y pacifistas del mundo se ponen mas alertos ante tal conducta de Japon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El pais isleno debe darse clara cuenta de ello y dejar de incurrir en esas imprudentes acciones.
